    "millsfield:images_texts": [
      "ADANI\nKingmhn\nDONG KINGMAN",
      "Cocktailso\nSherry Dubonnet Campari\nManhattan Gin Martini Vodka Martini Vermouth\nBloody Mary Screwdriver Whiskey Sour\nTom Collins Vodka Collins Daiquiri Scotch\nBourbon\nCanadian Gin Vodka Rum Premium Beer\nMenus\nApéritif\nSelected Gourmet Delicacies\nRoast au Vol\nA selected cut of aged beef. lamb or other succulent meat\nroasted on board and carved to order\nYour flight attendant will advise you of today's roast\nDuckling Cointreau\nDelicate duckling in a rich orange sauce laced with liqueurs\nChicken Madeira\nTender chicken with walnuts, raisins and a lush Madeira sauce\nTrout Meunière\nCold water trout sautéed with butter, lemon and fresh parsiey\nPlat du Jour\nSpecialty of the day\nButtered Vegetable Bouquet\nRice Pilaf",
      "Coffee\nChicken Madeira\nTender chicken with walnuts, raisins and a lush Madeira sauce\nTrout Meunière\nCold water trout sautéed with butter. lemon and fresh parsie\nPlat du Jour\nSpecialty of the day\nButtered Vegetable Bouquet\nRice Pilaf\nPotatoes Maison\nTossed Garden Salad\nFruit Basket\nSelection of Cheeses\nDessert\nTea\nDecaffeinated Coffee\nDrambuie\nSelected Red and White Wines\nChampagne Brut\nAmaretto di Saronno Bénédictine\nCrème de Menthe Cognac VSOP\nCointreau",
      "JAPAN\nDong Kingman, the award winning Chinese-American artist, travels the world sketching and painting\nthe beautiful, the monumental and the picturesque. His watercolors grace more than forty\npermanent museum and private collections in the USA and abroad.\nJAPAN is a land of contrasts. It can display the most neon-lit, skyscrapered and expressway-lined\nface, vet finds its inspiration in the quiet beauty of the graceful Tori Gate and Mt. Fuji, pictured here.\nThe Japanese can run their trains at lightening speed, yet spend hours on a small conversational\ncourtesy. Here you will find graceful perfection and formality contrasted with vigorous commerce.\nAmong the many stylish hotels in the capital city of Tokyo is the Keio Plaza Inter-Continental.\nPan Am serves Tokyo on its Round-The-World flights and nonstop daily from New York, San Francisco,\nLos Angeles, Honolulu, and Hong Kong. Osaka is served nonstop from Honolulu.\n@PAN AM"
    ],
